BFN 

  [Text] Rome, May 17 -- Poland's Prime Minister Waldemar 
Pawlak, now on a visit to Rome, met on Tuesday [17 May] with 
Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi. 
  After a forty-minute talk which focused on economic issues, 
the Italian prime minister declared that Italy was interested in 
developing economic cooperation with Poland and announced that 
his government would support Polish efforts to join the European 
Union. 
  Prime Minister Pawlak told newsmen that he had discussed 
with 
Berlusconi the question of actions which would bring Poland into 
the group of lower investment risk countries. He also said that 
he had invited the Italian Prime Minister to visit Poland 
shortly. 
  Later in the day, the Polish Prime Minister met for talks 
with "Fiat" car-maker president Giovanni Agnelli. 

